The paper is about unsupervised image retrieval using deep learning algorithms on irregular graphs. This topic falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of sparse coding techniques, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper evaluates its method on benchmark datasets, which is a common practice in multimedia (cs.MM) research.
